seven samurai ( 七人の侍 shichinin no samurai ) is a 1954 japanese samurai adventure drama film co-written , edited , and directed by akira kurosawa . the story takes place in 1586 during the sengoku period of japanese history . it follows the story of a village of farmers that hire seven ronin ( masterless samurai ) to combat bandits who will return after the harvest to steal their crops . since its release , seven samurai has consistently ranked highly in critics ' lists of the greatest films , such as the bfi 's sight & sound and rotten tomatoes polls . it has remained highly influential , often seen as one of the most " remade , reworked , referenced " films in cinema .